p: A total of 4 cyclic peptides (peaks 41, 43, 46, and 51) were identified in this study, and the compounds 41, 43, 46, and 51 showed [M + H] + ion at m/z 679.51224, 792.59618, 905.68109, and 1018.76517, respectively. They have similar fragmentation pathways [ 14]. This is the first time to report the cyclic peptide from D. dentiger.
